{{Infobox Chinese|t=加拿大華裔軍事博物館<ref name=CCMMSpage>"[http://www.ccmms.ca/about-us/ About Us]" ([https://www.webcitation.org/6Vx76DOQb Archive]). Chinese Canadian Military Museum Society. Retrieved on January 29, 2015. [http://www.ccmms.ca/wp-content/themes/ccmms/images/bg_logo.jpg See logo image] ([https://www.webcitation.org/6Vx7LwoHm Archive])</ref>|s=加拿大华裔军事博物馆|p=Jiānádà Huáyì Jūnshì Bówùguǎn}} The '''Chinese Canadian Military Museum Society''' (CCMMS) is located in Vancouver, on the second floor of the [[Chinese Cultural Centre, Vancouver|Chinese Cultural Centre]].<ref>"[http://royalbcmuseum.bc.ca/assets/2013-11-01-Remembrance-Weekend-2013-Release-Final.pdf A Weekend of Remembrance at the Royal BC Museum]" ([https://www.webcitation.org/6Vx1RcB0N Archive]). ''[[Royal BC Museum]]''. Retrieved on January 29, 2013. p. 1/3.</ref> It was created in 1998 and maintains a museum in that city.<ref name="CCMMSpage"/>
The museum has given temporary displays to the [[Canadian War Museum]] in [[Ottawa]].<ref>Uechi, Jenny. "On Remembrance Day, Chinese Canadians recall struggle for citizenship and equality." ''[[Vancouver Observer]]''. November 12, 2012. p. [http://www.vancouverobserver.com/world/canada/remembrance-day-chinese-canadians-recall-struggle-citizenship-and-equality 1]. Retrieved on January 29, 2015.</ref>
